Tsaron tsaro a waje da Ofishin Jakadancin Amurka a Chengdu, China
Akwai tsananin tsaro a wajen ofishin jakadancin Amurka a birnin Chengdu, China a ranar Lahadi, yayin da ma'aikatan Amurka ke shirin barin ginin.
An ga manyan motoci uku suna shiga ginin, yayin da 'yan sanda masu riguna da tufafi na farar hula suka yi layi a bangarorin biyu na titi, waɗanda aka yi wa katanga na ƙarfe.
Editan jaridar China ta Global Times ta wallafa a shafinta na Twitter cewa an ba da sa'o'i 72 don rufe ofishin jakadancin Amurka a Chengdu, ko kuma har zuwa karfe 10 na safe (0200 GMT) a ranar Litinin, 27 ga watan Yuli.
Kasar Sin ta zargi wasu ma'aikatan ofishin jakadancin Chengdu da "yin ayyuka da ba su jitu da sunayensu ba".
Ba tare da ya ba da cikakken bayani ba, kakakin ma'aikatar harkokin wajen kasar Sin, Wang Wenbin ya ce irin wannan aikin ya tsoma baki a harkokin kasar Sin kuma ya cutar da bukatun tsaro.
An bayar da umarnin da kasar Sin ta bayar na rufe ofishin jakadancin kasar a Chengdu a ranar Juma'a a matsayin sakamako ga umarnin da Amurka ta bayar na rufe ofishin jakadancin kasar Sin a Houston, Texas.
Washington ta umurci kasar Sin ta rufe ofishin Houston "don kare dukiyar ilimi ta Amurka da kuma bayanan sirri na Amurkawa".
Yayin da aka rufe ofishin jakadancin kasar Sin a Houston a ranar Juma'a, an ga wasu maza da suka bayyana a matsayin jami'an Amurka sun shiga cikin ginin ta hanyar ƙofar baya.
Wang ya ce a ranar Asabar cewa ya keta yarjejeniyar kasa da kasa da kuma ta biyu kuma kasar Sin za ta amsa, ba tare da bayyana yadda ba.
Rufe-rufe-rufe ya kara daɗa tashin hankali tsakanin ƙasashen biyu kan batutuwan kasuwanci da leken asiri na masana'antu zuwa haƙƙin ɗan adam.
Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta ce dubban 'yan bindiga na Pakistan a Afghanistan
Islamabad -- Rahoton Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya ce sama da 'yan tawaye Pakistan 6,000 na boye a Afghanistan, mafi yawansu na kungiyar Taliban ta Pakistan da ke da alhakin kai hare-hare ga sojojin Pakistan da kuma fararen hula.
Rahoton da aka fitar a wannan makon ya ce kungiyar, da aka sani da Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP), ta yi alaka da kungiyar ta Islamic State da ke Afghanistan.
Wasu daga cikin mambobin TTP sun ma shiga kungiyar IS, wadda ke da hedkwatarta a gabashin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghanistan ba ta amsa a ranar Lahadi ga buƙatun Associated Press don yin tsokaci ba.
Rahoton ya ce IS a Afghanistan, wanda aka sani da IS a lardin Khorasan, an yi masa mummunan rauni daga sojojin tsaro na Afghanistan da kuma sojojin Amurka da NATO, har ma da Taliban na Afghanistan a wasu lokuta.
Hukumar Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da ke kula da takunkumin da ake amfani da su wajen bincike da kuma saka idanu kan 'yan ta'adda a duniya ce ta shirya rahoton.
Rahoton ya kimanta yawan 'yan kungiyar IS a Afghanistan zuwa 2,200, kuma yayin da jagorancin ta ya ƙare, IS har yanzu tana kirga tsakanin shugabannin ta dan asalin Syria Abu Said Mohammad al-Khorasani.
Rahoton ya kuma ce tawagar sa ido ta samu bayani cewa manyan kwamandan kungiyar Islama Abu Qutaibah da Abu Hajar al-Iraqi sun isa Afghanistan kwanan nan daga Gabas ta Tsakiya.
